## Description
Include validation errors in FailedSopSequence

```
{
    "00081198": {
        "vr": "SQ",
        "Value": [
            {
                "00081150": {
                    "vr": "UI",
                    "Value": [
                        "dgdgdf"
                    ]
                },
                "00081155": {
                    "vr": "UI",
                    "Value": [
                        "1.3.6.1.4.1.45096.dfgdfgdfgdfgdfgdf"
                    ]
                },
                "00081197": {
                    "vr": "US",
                    "Value": [
                        43264
                    ]
                },
                "00741048": {
                    "vr": "SQ",
                    "Value": [
                        {
                            "00000902": {
                                "vr": "LO",
                                "Value": [
                                    "DICOM100: (0008,0020) - Dicom element 'StudyDate' failed validation for VR 'DA': Value cannot be parsed as a valid date."
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "00000902": {
                                "vr": "LO",
                                "Value": [
                                    "DICOM100: (0008,1155) - Dicom element 'SOPInstanceUID' failed validation for VR 'UI': DICOM Identifier is invalid. Value length should not exceed the maximum length of 64 characters. Value should contain characters in '0'-'9' and '.'. Each component must start with non-zero number."
                                ]
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }
        ]
    }
}
```
As part of this work

- Removed existing Exception property which gets thrown on first error.
- Updated tests
## Related issues
